# Chat Support (Claude + Supabase + Kognitos API Tools)

## Architecture

```
App sidebar "Conversations" group (client) Ōåö useChat hook Ōåö ChatProvider context
  ŌåÆ POST /api/chat ŌåÆ Claude (Anthropic) streaming with API tools ŌåÆ Kognitos REST API
  ŌåÆ SSE stream back to client (token-by-token)
  ŌåÆ Messages persisted in Supabase
```

Sessions and messages persist in Supabase. Claude answers questions using **registered API tools only** ŌĆö it never runs arbitrary code. The chat UI lives at `/chat` with conversation history always visible in the app sidebar.

## Registered Tools

| Tool | API endpoint | Purpose |
|------|-------------|---------|
| `list_runs` | GET /automations/{id}/runs | List batch history with statuses |
| `get_run` | GET /automations/{id}/runs/{runId} | Full run details: decoded outputs, errors |
| `get_automation` | GET /automations/{id} | Get automation code, connections, inputs |

To add a new tool, define an `Anthropic.Tool` in the `TOOLS` array in `app/api/chat/route.ts` and add its handler to the `executeTool` switch. Update the system prompt in `lib/chat/system-prompt.ts` to describe it.

### Customizing tools for your domain

The template ships with generic `list_runs`, `get_run`, and `get_automation` tools that call the Kognitos API directly. When building a specific app:

1. **Rename tools** to use domain language (e.g. `list_runs` ŌåÆ `list_referrals`, `get_run` ŌåÆ `get_invoice`)
2. **Update descriptions** ŌĆö Claude uses these to decide when to call a tool
3. **Replace `executeTool` handlers** ŌĆö call your domain-specific data-fetching functions (e.g. `fetchReferrals()`) instead of raw API calls, especially if you need Arrow IPC decoding or field transformation
4. **Add domain-specific tools** ŌĆö e.g. `search_by_patient_name`, `get_statistics`, `list_exceptions`

## Required env vars

- `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` ŌĆö Claude API key
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` ŌĆö Supabase project URL
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` ŌĆö Supabase anon key
- `SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` ŌĆö Supabase service role key (server-side only)
- `KOGNITOS_TOKEN` ŌĆö Kognitos API bearer token

## Required npm packages

- `@anthropic-ai/sdk` ŌĆö Anthropic Claude SDK
- `@supabase/supabase-js` ŌĆö Supabase client
- `@kognitos/lattice` ŌĆö Lattice UI components (installed from local `.tgz`)
- `react-markdown` + `remark-gfm` ŌĆö Markdown rendering (alternative to Lattice `Markdown`)
